WEBVTT

00:06.333 --> 00:08.833
NETFLIX PRESENTS

01:35.208 --> 01:36.291
BASED ON THE BOOK
"THE CATHOLIC SCHOOL"

01:36.375 --> 01:37.708
BY EDOARDO ALBINATI
PUBLISHED BY RIZZOLI

02:42.375 --> 02:43.500
Get us out!

02:43.583 --> 02:44.583
Please!

02:51.583 --> 02:53.625
Please, don't go away.

02:55.041 --> 02:56.416
Otherwise, they'll be back.

02:58.625 --> 02:59.625
Please.

03:11.958 --> 03:15.875
6 MONTHS BEFORE THE FACTS

03:26.416 --> 03:28.041
<i>I couldn't say when it all began.</i>

03:28.125 --> 03:29.541
Get in line!

03:29.625 --> 03:31.208
<i>But that story was about us all.</i>

03:31.291 --> 03:32.166
Back straight!

03:32.250 --> 03:36.208
<i>Our education,</i>
<i>our neighborhood, our school.</i>

03:36.875 --> 03:38.875
<i>After that,</i>
<i>nothing would ever be the same.</i>

03:38.958 --> 03:40.583
One, two.

03:45.166 --> 03:47.333
Let me hear your voice.

03:47.416 --> 03:48.666
One, two!

03:51.291 --> 03:54.625
<i>I was in my junior year</i>
<i>at a private high school,</i>

03:54.708 --> 03:56.500
<i>with a monthly tuition to pay.</i>

03:57.666 --> 03:59.291
<i>Girls weren't allowed to attend.</i>

03:59.375 --> 04:02.791
<i>We were all boys</i>
<i>from a middle-class neighborhood of Rome.</i>

04:02.875 --> 04:04.250
<i>Daddy's boys, essentially.</i>

04:04.333 --> 04:06.291
<i>One of my classmates was Salvatore,</i>

04:06.375 --> 04:08.750
<i>Angelo's brother,</i>
<i>who was a year older than us.</i>

04:08.833 --> 04:10.250
Let me see some strength!

04:11.500 --> 04:12.625
<i>And then Picchiatello,</i>

04:13.125 --> 04:14.833
<i>so called because he was a very weird guy.</i>

04:14.916 --> 04:17.750
<i>His mom was an actress</i>
<i>we all fantasized about.</i>

04:19.083 --> 04:20.500
<i>Gioacchino Rummo.</i>

04:21.000 --> 04:22.375
<i>Perhaps the only one who believed</i>

04:22.458 --> 04:24.833
<i>in the Christian values</i>
<i>that priests were trying to teach us.</i>

04:25.416 --> 04:26.791
<i>Except Brother Curzio.</i>

04:26.875 --> 04:29.333
<i>If you looked closely,</i>
<i>he didn't even seem a priest.</i>

04:29.416 --> 04:30.791
Running on the spot!

04:30.875 --> 04:32.291
One, two!

04:32.791 --> 04:35.541
Arbus, these are spasms, not gymnastics!

04:35.625 --> 04:38.666
Where are you going? Come on!

04:38.750 --> 04:41.583
One, two!

04:44.208 --> 04:46.833
<i>It was 1975,</i>

04:46.916 --> 04:48.958
<i>and violence was commonplace.</i>

05:04.875 --> 05:06.000
What happened, Pik?

05:09.791 --> 05:10.666
Romoli.

05:14.791 --> 05:18.000
He blew himself up
in front of the headmaster.

05:18.083 --> 05:21.541
-Oh, it's true!
-Grow up! Become a man, once and for all!

05:24.458 --> 05:25.333
D'Avenia.

05:31.750 --> 05:33.666
Let me guess,
you didn't see anything, did you?

05:33.750 --> 05:34.916
Like everyone else?

05:35.416 --> 05:37.875
One of your mates is attacked
in the courtyard

05:37.958 --> 05:39.625
and no one has seen a thing.

05:43.583 --> 05:44.458
Fine.

05:47.333 --> 05:49.375
If you have nothing to say, you can go.

06:00.250 --> 06:01.750
Romoli wasn't bothering anyone.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.625
As soon as the bell rang,

06:05.333 --> 06:07.416
the seniors approached him

06:07.916 --> 06:10.333
and surrounded him,
so nobody could see what they were doing.

06:10.416 --> 06:12.625
At first, they just gave him a few slaps.

06:13.333 --> 06:15.750
Then one grabbed his shirt
and started tugging at him.

06:19.416 --> 06:21.833
So his glasses just dropped off?

06:21.916 --> 06:22.791
No.

06:23.708 --> 06:25.166
They broke them on purpose.

06:25.666 --> 06:26.583
Good.

06:28.291 --> 06:29.416
Now tell me who did it.

06:30.166 --> 06:33.000
-No. Ask Jervi. He's the one who sent--
-Hey.

06:34.416 --> 06:35.916
I can hear it from you first.

07:06.375 --> 07:07.375
Guido.

07:07.458 --> 07:09.166
Your father is with the headmaster.

07:16.833 --> 07:19.833
They're young, but they have to understand
that we have rules here.

07:19.916 --> 07:23.041
Your parents decided
to send you to this school

07:23.125 --> 07:26.041
because obviously what they want for you

07:26.125 --> 07:28.875
is a safe harbor.

07:28.958 --> 07:33.208
Something to shelter you
from the… moral drift that--

07:33.291 --> 07:34.791
Headmaster, excuse me.

07:34.875 --> 07:38.916
Have you already started collecting
donations for Holy Easter, or…

07:42.541 --> 07:43.458
Not yet, but…

07:43.541 --> 07:44.500
Let me know.

07:46.041 --> 07:47.125
Let's go now.

07:47.208 --> 07:48.750
We won't trouble you further. Thank you.

07:49.583 --> 07:50.416
Gianni.

07:51.041 --> 07:52.875
Tell the janitor to send Jervi in.

08:04.083 --> 08:05.416
What got into you?

08:08.750 --> 08:09.875
What did I tell you?

08:14.166 --> 08:15.041
So?

08:19.166 --> 08:21.041
You made me look like a fucking moron.

08:22.833 --> 08:24.583
Come here.

08:24.666 --> 08:27.208
What did I tell you?

08:29.250 --> 08:31.625
Don't you ever dare to do it again!

08:32.708 --> 08:34.125
You must never do it again!

08:34.208 --> 08:35.541
I got it. Sorry.

08:36.416 --> 08:38.000
You made me look like a fucking moron.

08:39.083 --> 08:40.291
Like a fucking moron.

08:40.375 --> 08:42.291
From tomorrow, things will change.

08:44.125 --> 08:45.916
<i>Our life was full of rules.</i>

08:46.958 --> 08:49.166
<i>When we broke them,</i>
<i>sometimes we were punished,</i>

08:49.250 --> 08:50.916
<i>and other times nothing happened.</i>

08:51.416 --> 08:54.625
<i>So we wondered if those rules</i>
<i>had been established at random.</i>

08:55.958 --> 08:59.083
<i>When you turn six, you leave</i>
<i>your family shell and enter school.</i>

08:59.166 --> 09:00.208
<i>Another shell.</i>

09:01.583 --> 09:04.458
<i>In school, you risked acquiring</i>
<i>one of two attitudes.</i>

09:04.958 --> 09:07.333
<i>Subdue or be subdued.</i>

09:08.208 --> 09:10.166
Give them back!
Rachele, you can't take them.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.125
-Stop it.
-You're always stealing from me.

09:12.208 --> 09:13.791
Enough! I'll tell Mom.

09:13.875 --> 09:15.166
Stop it.

09:15.250 --> 09:17.250
-No!
-Mom, Rachele stole my shoes.

09:17.333 --> 09:18.625
That's not true! Don't lie.

09:18.708 --> 09:20.500
I don't care. You two sort it out.

09:20.583 --> 09:23.375
Elisabetta,
can you turn off the oven, please?

09:23.458 --> 09:24.791
-I'll be right there.
-Okay.

09:25.291 --> 09:27.583
Toby. Come on, go with them.

09:28.375 --> 09:29.208
So?

09:29.291 --> 09:31.333
So, I don't understand.

09:31.416 --> 09:33.083
They didn't do anything to them.

09:33.583 --> 09:35.208
They didn't take any action.

09:35.291 --> 09:37.833
They'll just buy him
a new pair of glasses and that's it.

09:38.333 --> 09:39.208
And it's done.

09:39.291 --> 09:41.583
What do you think
they should have done to them?

09:42.166 --> 09:44.208
Humiliate them in front of everyone?
Suspend them?

09:44.291 --> 09:46.791
What did human justice do to the Lord?

09:47.500 --> 09:50.166
It treated Him with hatred,
with thirst for revenge.

09:50.250 --> 09:51.958
Evil begets more evil.

09:52.041 --> 09:56.125
The behavior of Gioacchino's mates
must be understood and forgiven.

09:56.208 --> 09:58.291
Or we'll enter a spiral
from which we'll never escape.

09:58.375 --> 10:00.666
Sorry, Dad.
Aren't you the one who keeps saying

10:00.750 --> 10:03.625
that forgiveness should only
be granted after confession?

10:03.708 --> 10:08.000
Yes. But I also tell you not to put
too much trust in perfection.

10:08.791 --> 10:09.791
No, I'm good.

10:09.875 --> 10:11.666
And take heed of prejudices.

10:11.750 --> 10:13.375
Enough arguing.

10:14.083 --> 10:15.125
Girls. Here. Good girl.

10:15.208 --> 10:17.250
Giaele, food's ready.

10:22.416 --> 10:25.208
In the name of the Father,
the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

10:40.125 --> 10:41.166
I'm not in the mood.

10:43.125 --> 10:44.125
Why?

10:45.000 --> 10:46.916
Because I'm fertile right now.

10:47.791 --> 10:50.166
And it's not a good time
to have another baby.

10:50.791 --> 10:52.625
Well, why not?

10:52.708 --> 10:54.875
I'm the one who'll have to carry it.

10:57.333 --> 10:59.041
We've already discussed this.

10:59.125 --> 11:00.125
Please.

11:13.708 --> 11:15.333
Hey! Big hair!

11:17.541 --> 11:20.041
-We got him in front of everyone.
-Glasses?

11:20.708 --> 11:22.708
Snap! Tomorrow they'll have tape on.

11:29.416 --> 11:31.250
-How did it go with your dad?
-As usual.

11:31.333 --> 11:34.541
He gave me a fucking hard time,
but in the end, he stopped.

11:34.625 --> 11:36.250
He said he won't let me out anymore.

11:36.750 --> 11:37.791
And you, Giampie'?

11:38.375 --> 11:39.708
Not a word.

11:39.791 --> 11:41.291
-For real?
-Obviously.

11:41.375 --> 11:43.375
-Your granddad built the school.
-Exactly.

11:43.458 --> 11:45.208
And my dad gives them money every year.

11:45.291 --> 11:47.958
The headmaster
should just shut his mouth. That's it.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.166
They're pissing me off.

11:50.500 --> 11:51.416
Well said, Angelo!

11:51.500 --> 11:52.708
-Wanna get a drink?
-Yes.

11:52.791 --> 11:53.625
Okay. Well…

11:54.291 --> 11:55.291
Angelo.

11:56.166 --> 11:58.541
-Andrea is about to be released from jail.
-What?

11:58.625 --> 11:59.916
I've just been told.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.125
It's gonna be soon.

12:03.333 --> 12:05.041
Are we gonna be here all night?

12:05.125 --> 12:05.958
Any ideas?

12:06.041 --> 12:07.166
I don't know, really.

12:07.250 --> 12:09.208
Let's decide something. Let's do…

12:09.291 --> 12:11.500
In fact, I think I do have an idea.

12:13.916 --> 12:15.708
Put it back!

12:20.750 --> 12:21.958
Angelo.

12:22.041 --> 12:24.000
-What?
-Where have you been?

12:24.083 --> 12:26.625
Where do you think I've been?
With my friends.

12:27.250 --> 12:29.166
Why do you always make me worry?

12:29.250 --> 12:31.375
Worry about what? I'm here with you.

12:31.458 --> 12:32.625
Let's go to bed.

12:43.916 --> 12:45.916
I know you're awake.

12:48.375 --> 12:50.791
Gianni told me what happened at school.

12:50.875 --> 12:51.916
What did he tell you?

12:52.416 --> 12:53.625
That they questioned you.

12:53.708 --> 12:54.541
Yes.

12:55.291 --> 12:58.208
The headmaster kept us at school
because he wanted to know who did it.

12:59.166 --> 13:00.750
-And did you tell him?
-No.

13:00.833 --> 13:01.666
Are you sure?

13:04.541 --> 13:05.708
Well done.

13:05.791 --> 13:07.000
You kept your mouth shut.

13:07.875 --> 13:09.166
Never be a snitch.

13:10.708 --> 13:12.750
-Understood?
-Yes.

13:14.666 --> 13:15.500
Yes, what?

13:16.166 --> 13:17.958
One should never be a snitch.

13:28.791 --> 13:30.875
<i>Any other sins to confess?</i>

13:31.708 --> 13:33.083
<i>I tell a lot of lies.</i>

13:33.166 --> 13:34.041
<i>That's bad.</i>

13:34.625 --> 13:36.250
Lying is a serious sin.

13:38.333 --> 13:39.875
What kind of lies?

13:41.166 --> 13:42.208
All kinds.

13:45.416 --> 13:47.250
In order to be accepted by others.

13:49.458 --> 13:51.666
<i>I pretend to have the same passions.</i>

13:52.416 --> 13:53.583
<i>The same ideas.</i>

13:55.458 --> 13:57.916
<i>I wish I didn't do it.</i>
<i>It makes things worse for me, Father.</i>

13:58.000 --> 14:00.166
ST LUIGI HIGH SCHOOL

14:00.250 --> 14:01.875
<i>Because in the end I feel lonely.</i>

14:02.375 --> 14:04.500
It may seem
like I'm at ease with everyone.

14:06.333 --> 14:08.250
And I get along with everyone.

14:10.666 --> 14:13.041
But I'm never
really comfortable with anyone.

14:16.916 --> 14:19.041
I am never really myself, Father.

14:32.500 --> 14:35.333
You seriously told him in confession
that you don't believe in God?

14:35.916 --> 14:37.416
What if he reports you?

14:37.500 --> 14:39.500
I'm leaving this school, anyway.

14:39.583 --> 14:41.916
I'm not learning anything.
I don't trust the teachers.

14:42.500 --> 14:45.333
They should know stuff,
yet they don't even know they don't know.

14:45.416 --> 14:46.708
They assume.

14:46.791 --> 14:48.916
Their authority is based on nothing.

14:49.750 --> 14:51.000
So, who do you trust?

14:54.625 --> 14:55.625
I trust you.

14:57.666 --> 14:59.583
You've chosen the wrong person.

15:00.083 --> 15:03.041
Now it's reduced
to a simple quadratic equation.

15:03.666 --> 15:06.750
Which I assume
you all know very well, right?

15:07.333 --> 15:08.583
So what's your plan?

15:08.666 --> 15:11.041
Once you've solved the equation…

15:11.125 --> 15:12.333
I'll do two years in one.

15:13.083 --> 15:14.833
I'll get my diploma one year early.

15:15.333 --> 15:18.458
You need to have a B average
in all sophomore subjects.

15:18.541 --> 15:21.208
-And take all junior-year exams.
-I know.

15:21.291 --> 15:22.291
Arbus!

15:23.125 --> 15:26.333
Since you're so chatty
this morning, come here.

15:26.416 --> 15:28.708
Solve the equation for us. Come on.

15:41.125 --> 15:42.083
This one?

15:42.708 --> 15:43.541
Yes.

16:01.208 --> 16:02.375
<i>Arbus.</i>

16:02.916 --> 16:04.875
<i>He was seen as a phenomenon by us all.</i>

16:04.958 --> 16:08.083
<i>He was worshiped,</i>
<i>and thus kept at a distance.</i>

16:08.166 --> 16:09.416
Okay, Arbus.

16:09.500 --> 16:10.833
You may return to your seat.

16:11.625 --> 16:14.416
<i>The greatest thing about Arbus</i>
<i>is that he would never flinch</i>

16:14.500 --> 16:15.875
<i>and never lose hope.</i>

16:16.625 --> 16:18.708
<i>Arbus was admired by all of us.</i>

16:20.041 --> 16:22.000
<i>Jervi was too, but for other reasons.</i>

17:24.916 --> 17:26.583
-The body of Christ.
-Amen.

17:30.333 --> 17:32.166
-The body of Christ.
-Amen.

17:33.500 --> 17:35.291
The body of Christ.

17:42.583 --> 17:43.666
Mom.

17:44.583 --> 17:45.416
What?

17:45.500 --> 17:48.666
-Why can't I take the communion?
-Because you can't, sweetheart.

17:49.833 --> 17:50.791
But why?

17:52.458 --> 17:55.208
It's the way it is.
When you grow up, I'll explain it to you.

17:55.291 --> 17:56.833
-The body of Christ.
-Amen.

17:57.916 --> 17:59.083
Let's pray.

17:59.166 --> 18:01.500
In the name of Christ, Our Lord.

18:02.250 --> 18:03.875
Amen.

18:06.208 --> 18:07.500
-Gioacchino.
-Yes?

18:07.583 --> 18:09.750
Where are your schoolmates?

18:09.833 --> 18:11.458
Don't they attend Mass?

18:11.541 --> 18:13.625
They attend the compulsory ones at school.

18:16.458 --> 18:19.166
What's the point of sending their kids
to a Catholic school?

18:19.250 --> 18:21.208
Maybe their parents work.
They don't have time.

18:21.291 --> 18:24.750
I get it, but not one
out of 20 boys. It's absurd.

18:26.000 --> 18:28.208
APOLLINAIRE'S IMMORAL TALES

18:29.833 --> 18:31.166
Mom!

18:32.750 --> 18:34.875
-Sweetheart.
-Didn't you see the car?

18:34.958 --> 18:36.458
What would I do without you?

18:37.250 --> 18:39.791
-Hey, are you all right?
-Yes, I'm fine.

18:43.000 --> 18:48.541
5 MONTHS BEFORE THE FACTS

19:01.291 --> 19:04.666
We could build a nice little house here
if we get the permits.

19:04.750 --> 19:05.750
Right?

19:06.583 --> 19:09.750
We could split the property.
One for you, one for your brother.

19:09.833 --> 19:10.791
That'd be nice.

19:12.916 --> 19:14.125
It could work.

19:18.916 --> 19:19.916
Look.

19:26.916 --> 19:27.916
Ruma.

19:34.375 --> 19:35.375
Again.

19:38.250 --> 19:39.208
You get emotional.

19:40.541 --> 19:43.083
I've told you many times.
You have to be cold-blooded.

19:43.958 --> 19:44.833
You aim.

19:45.791 --> 19:46.791
You shoot.

19:47.708 --> 19:48.666
Let's go.

19:52.791 --> 19:57.833
<i>The three pillars of our education</i>
<i>were persuasion, threat, and punishment.</i>

19:59.666 --> 20:01.750
<i>But they were more</i>
<i>like steps than pillars.</i>

20:01.833 --> 20:05.583
<i>If explanations and threats failed,</i>
<i>we then had to be punished.</i>

20:07.291 --> 20:10.375
<i>In my neighborhood, great ambitions</i>
<i>were either lacking altogether</i>

20:10.458 --> 20:12.750
<i>or manifested themselves catastrophically.</i>

20:13.500 --> 20:14.666
<i>The underlying moral was</i>

20:14.750 --> 20:18.000
<i>that everything that was transient</i>
<i>was unbearable.</i>

20:18.083 --> 20:21.500
<i>And since everything is transient,</i>
<i>everything was ultimately unbearable.</i>

20:21.583 --> 20:22.916
<i>Except in Arbus' family.</i>

20:23.000 --> 20:23.916
Good morning.

20:24.000 --> 20:26.541
<i>His father taught</i>
<i>mathematical logic at university.</i>

20:26.625 --> 20:29.625
<i>He seemed more interested in his students</i>
<i>than in his children.</i>

20:29.708 --> 20:30.625
Okay.

20:34.000 --> 20:35.583
This is identical to your house.

20:35.666 --> 20:37.583
My dad built it for my sister.

20:38.166 --> 20:40.416
He was obsessed
with a hacksaw and balsa wood.

20:57.000 --> 20:57.875
Come on.

21:01.791 --> 21:03.791
<i>Bonjour. </i>I've brought you a snack.

21:03.875 --> 21:05.166
Mom, please.

21:05.250 --> 21:06.500
<i>Monsieur.</i>

21:06.583 --> 21:08.000
Hello, ma'am. I'm Edoardo.

21:08.083 --> 21:09.083
Hey, Edoardo.

21:09.166 --> 21:10.166
How is it?

21:14.458 --> 21:16.166
My son is so absentminded.

21:16.250 --> 21:17.750
What's in this big head of yours?

21:17.833 --> 21:19.083
Secrets?

21:20.083 --> 21:21.875
No, no secrets, of course.

21:23.166 --> 21:24.708
What about you, Edoardo?

21:24.791 --> 21:26.375
Do you have secrets?

21:26.458 --> 21:27.375
Me?

21:27.458 --> 21:29.583
Yes, things you don't tell your mom.

21:29.666 --> 21:31.291
What are they? Tell me.

21:32.375 --> 21:34.583
Actually, I hardly tell her anything.

21:35.875 --> 21:36.875
So…

21:37.666 --> 21:38.750
Of course.

21:39.583 --> 21:40.916
What are you studying?

21:41.000 --> 21:42.041
Chemistry.

21:43.666 --> 21:44.541
Well,

21:44.625 --> 21:48.916
since we know chemistry already,
how about a game of poker?

22:04.291 --> 22:05.333
Ten thousand.

22:05.416 --> 22:06.333
Call.

22:07.541 --> 22:08.458
Fold.

22:11.916 --> 22:12.916
Two pairs.

22:16.375 --> 22:17.375
Straight.

22:47.000 --> 22:48.625
Put that stupid sword down.

22:48.708 --> 22:49.916
You'll hurt yourself.

22:50.000 --> 22:51.875
Mom, don't you see how skilled I am?

22:58.875 --> 22:59.750
I'm hungry.

23:00.375 --> 23:01.416
Are you hungry?

23:01.500 --> 23:02.500
I'm hungry.

23:03.250 --> 23:05.250
Call Fernanda. I have a headache.

23:08.041 --> 23:09.291
Fernanda?

23:10.791 --> 23:11.625
Fernanda?

23:11.708 --> 23:13.541
Why are you shouting? I told you…

23:13.625 --> 23:14.791
Fernanda!

23:14.875 --> 23:16.291
I have a headache.

