They've left.

1:36:25.625 --> 1:36:26.625
Rosaria.

1:36:28.750 --> 1:36:29.875
They've left.

1:36:32.875 --> 1:36:33.833
Rosaria.

1:36:35.291 --> 1:36:36.375
Wake up.

1:36:36.916 --> 1:36:38.166
Wake up, please.

1:37:18.291 --> 1:37:19.875
Please. Rosa'.

1:37:19.958 --> 1:37:21.083
Please.

1:37:25.583 --> 1:37:28.083
Help. I'm here.

1:37:29.125 --> 1:37:30.250
We're here.

1:37:30.333 --> 1:37:31.708
Please, open up.

1:37:31.791 --> 1:37:34.000
Otherwise, they'll be back. Please.

1:37:41.583 --> 1:37:43.166
Good evening. What's the matter?

1:37:43.250 --> 1:37:46.583
According to our records,
you're the owner of a white Fiat 127.

1:37:46.666 --> 1:37:47.750
Is it stolen?

1:37:47.833 --> 1:37:49.708
No, it's parked nearby.

1:37:49.791 --> 1:37:51.166
Are you the only one using it?

1:37:51.708 --> 1:37:53.291
No, my son uses it too. Why?

1:37:53.375 --> 1:37:55.875
-And where is he now?
-Asleep in his room.

1:37:57.000 --> 1:37:58.833
Sir, we have to check.

1:37:58.916 --> 1:37:59.916
Just a second.

1:38:01.541 --> 1:38:02.791
Raffaele, what's going on?

1:38:02.875 --> 1:38:04.125
Go to bed.

1:39:01.416 --> 1:39:06.791
<i>I confess to Almighty God</i>
<i>and to you, my brothers and sisters,</i>

1:39:08.666 --> 1:39:10.291
<i>that I have greatly sinned</i>

1:39:12.333 --> 1:39:16.291
in my thoughts and in my words,
in what I have done

1:39:17.416 --> 1:39:18.958
and in what I have failed to do.

1:39:20.541 --> 1:39:22.958
God Almighty, have mercy on us.

1:39:23.041 --> 1:39:25.166
Forgive our sins.

1:39:26.166 --> 1:39:29.875
<i>After these events,</i>
<i>some people suddenly reacted.</i>

1:39:31.791 --> 1:39:34.000
<i>It was as if the resentment</i>
<i>we all carried inside</i>

1:39:34.083 --> 1:39:36.250
<i>was looking for a way to emerge.</i>

1:39:38.458 --> 1:39:42.833
Jesus, who came to console the sinners…

1:39:42.916 --> 1:39:45.041
<i>I never went back to that high school.</i>

1:39:46.541 --> 1:39:47.916
<i>The last year, I left.</i>

1:39:49.625 --> 1:39:51.958
<i>After the murder,</i>
<i>our quiet neighborhood had changed.</i>

1:39:52.041 --> 1:39:54.416
<i>People in the street were suspicious.</i>

1:39:55.791 --> 1:39:57.750
<i>No one felt safe anymore.</i>

1:40:01.416 --> 1:40:05.833
SCIENCE ENLIGHTENS THE MIND

1:40:07.000 --> 1:40:09.041
<i>At home, every mother</i>
<i>scrutinized her child,</i>

1:40:09.125 --> 1:40:11.875
<i>trying to detect</i>
<i>if a monster was lurking in there too.</i>

1:40:15.833 --> 1:40:17.166
<i>This went on for a while.</i>

1:40:17.250 --> 1:40:18.416
<i>Everyone started to realize</i>

1:40:18.500 --> 1:40:20.458
<i>that if you sweep the dust</i>
<i>under the carpet,</i>

1:40:20.541 --> 1:40:22.000
<i>eventually a mountain piles up.</i>

1:40:25.250 --> 1:40:26.375
<i>Then, gradually,</i>

1:40:27.333 --> 1:40:29.291
<i>things went back to how they were before.</i>

1:41:14.791 --> 1:41:16.291
At the time of the Circeo Massacre,

1:41:16.375 --> 1:41:18.916
rape was not considered a crime
against the person,

1:41:19.000 --> 1:41:20.500
but against public morality.

1:41:20.583 --> 1:41:23.125
Rosaria Lopez’s death
and Donatella Colasanti’s torture

1:41:23.208 --> 1:41:26.083
ignited a debate that only concluded
in 1996, when Italian law was changed

1:41:26.166 --> 1:41:29.000
and sexual violence was finally considered
a crime against the person.

1:41:29.083 --> 1:41:33.208
The three perpetrators of the massacre
were all given life sentences.

1:41:33.708 --> 1:41:34.833
Angelo Izzo

1:41:34.916 --> 1:41:37.958
As soon as he was released on parole
for good conduct in 2005

1:41:38.041 --> 1:41:39.458
he killed two more women.

1:41:39.541 --> 1:41:40.416
Andrea Ghira

1:41:40.500 --> 1:41:42.958
died in Morocco in 1994
after eluding arrest

1:41:43.041 --> 1:41:45.416
and having lived all his life
as a fugitive.

1:41:45.500 --> 1:41:46.416
Gianni Guido

1:41:46.500 --> 1:41:50.333
Thanks to a sentence reduction,
he has been free since 2009.

1:41:52.458 --> 1:41:57.000
Donatella Colasanti passed away in 2005
at the age of just 47.

